\scaps The next day \scaps0 was quiet. During the morning Fay pursued the ostensible purpose of their visit by making biographical memoranda concerning the life of the late Son at the Propaganda Office.\par
Paddy visited Dane, the electrician, and took delivery of the ultra-violet projector.\par
Dane was proud of his work\emdash an aluminum case eight or nine inches on a side with a handle for carrying. Four lenses opened into the front, a power-pack fitted into clips at the back. In a row along the top were four tuners with vernier settings, four output valves, four switches.\par
"And is it accurate" Paddy asked skeptically.\par
"Accurate?" cried Dane. "It's as accurate as the Inter-world Standard that I calibrated it by! Three times I checked each one of the circuits and there's never an offbeat!"\par
